        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(clawdock): load docker-compose.override.yml",
        "body": "Fixes #49909.\n\n## Summary\n- Load `docker-compose.override.yml` when ClawDock helpers invoke Docker Compose with explicit `-f` args.\n- Keep `docker-compose.extra.yml` loaded after the standard override and document the order.\n- Add a regression test for `_clawdock_compose` argument construction.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run test/scripts/clawdock-helpers.test.ts`\n- `bash -n scripts/clawdock/clawdock-helpers.sh`\n- `zsh -n scripts/clawdock/clawdock-helpers.sh`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: ClawDock commands now include `docker-compose.override.yml` when present instead of silently ignoring it after explicit `-f` args disable Compose's default auto-merge.\nReal environment tested: macOS Darwin arm64 shell using official Docker Compose standalone v5.1.3 for `config` resolution, through the ClawDock helper's `docker compose` invocation path.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `CLAWDOCK_DIR=/private/tmp/openclaw-clawdock-real-proof-85313/project HOME=/private/tmp/openclaw-clawdock-real-proof-85313/home PATH=/private/tmp/openclaw-clawdock-real-proof-85313/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin bash -lc 'source scripts/clawdock/clawdock-helpers.sh; _clawdock_compose config --no-interpolate'`\nEvidence after fix: Real Docker Compose config output after the helper loaded `docker-compose.yml`, `docker-compose.override.yml`, and `docker-compose.extra.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nname: project\nnetworks:\n  default:\n    name: project_default\nservices:\n  proof:\n    environment:\n      - EXTRA_PRECEDENCE=extra\n      - OPENCLAW_COMPOSE_LAYER=override\n      - OVERRIDE_FILE_ACTIVE=yes\n      - EXTRA_FILE_ACTIVE=yes\n    image: alpine:3.20\n    networks:\n      default: null\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: `OVERRIDE_FILE_ACTIVE=yes` appears in the resolved Compose config, proving the standard override file is no longer ignored; `EXTRA_PRECEDENCE=extra` appears while `OPENCLAW_COMPOSE_LAYER=override` remains, proving `docker-compose.extra.yml` is loaded after the standard override and has final precedence for overlapping keys.\nWhat was not tested: `docker compose up` against a running Docker daemon; this proof exercises Compose file resolution with `config`, which is the behavior changed by this patch.",
